title: Appointments to Expert Committee on Food Safety
content_text:
p>
					The Government announced today (September 14) the 
					re-appointment of Professor Ma Ching-yung and Professor Chen 
					Zhen-yu as Chairman and Vice-Chairman of the Expert 
					Committee on Food Safety respectively. The Government also appointed six new members and 
					reappointed 14 incumbent members to the Expert Committee.
					 All appointments last for a term of two years with effect 
					from tomorrow (September 15). The six new members are all local representatives. They are

Mr Kenneth Chan Kin-nin, Dr Olivia Chan Sinn-kay, Mr Cheng 
					Kit-man, Mr Sunny Lee Wai-kwong, Dr Wendy Ma Lynn and Dr 
					Jennifer Wan Man-fan. Mr Chan is President of the Hong Kong Food Council. Dr Chan is a private practice veterinarian. She also serves 
					as a member of the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong 
					and the Animal Welfare Advisory Group of the Agriculture, 
					Fisheries and Conservation Department (AFCD). Mr Cheng is a retired senior physicist of the Department of

Health (DH). He is an expert in radiation. Mr Lee is Vice-President (Administration) of the City 
					University of Hong Kong. He is also Chairman of the 
					Committee on Information Technology Training and Development 
					of Vocational Training Council, and a member of the Risk 
					Communication Advisory Group of the DH's Centre for Health 
					Protection.  Dr Ma is senior programme director of the College of Life 
					Sciences and Technology of the HKU School of Professional

Sciences and Technology of the HKU School of Professional 
					and Continuing Education. She is also Vice-Chairperson of 
					the Hong Kong Dietitians Association. Dr Wan is Associate Professor of the School of Biological 
					Science of the University of Hong Kong. She is an expert in 
					nutrition and food sciences. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, said that 
					food safety is one of the priorities of the Government. He 
					looks forward to the views provided by members of the Expert

looks forward to the views provided by members of the Expert 
					Committee to the Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene 
					(DFEH) on matters relating to food safety. He also thanked the outgoing members, namely Dr Lawrence 
					Chan, Professor Annisa Lee, Dr Edmund Li, Ms Lina Lim, 
					Professor Leo Sin and Dr Wong Man-sau, for their invaluable 
					contribution to the Expert Committee.  The Expert Committee advises the DFEH on existing or new 
					food safety operational strategies and measures to protect

food safety operational strategies and measures to protect 
					public health. It also advises the DFEH on standards or 
					guidelines relating to food safety and food composition 
					having regard to international practices, trends and 
					developments. The membership list of the Expert Committee for the new term 
					is as below: Chairman: Professor Ma Ching-yung  Vice-Chairman: Professor Chen Zhen-yu
